Ahh, the sounds of love. Hearing the soundtrack to the romantic comedy 
Runaway Bride, you&#039;ll get plenty of them. The Dixie Chicks, Eric Clapton, 
Martina McBride, and Shawn Colvin all lend new tracks to this 
sometimes-rootsy, sometimes-pop compilation. U2&#039;s classic anthem "I Still 
Haven&#039;t Found What I&#039;m Looking For" starts things off, but Cupid quickly 
strikes with McBride&#039;s "I Love You," Clapton&#039;s intimate charmer "Blue Eyes 
Blue," and Marc Anthony&#039;s "You Sang to Me." Miles Davis&#039;s gorgeous "It Never 
Entered My Mind" is the one surprise cut, but the new tracks are the real 
highlight here. --Jason Verlinde
